iritual progress, in reaction \nto furth=\r\ner exchanges on Twitter. This is a delicate area where many have \nmisconcep=\r\ntions and I will try to address them. \n\n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nM=\r\naharshi Vasishtha&#39;s teaching to Lord Rama is clear in Yoga Vaasishtham. The=\r\n \ngoal of existence and sadhana is self-realization. Siddhis are to be neit=\r\nher \nspecifically sought nor specifically avoided, by a seeker of Self. If =\r\nNature \ngives one some siddhi(s), one should accept them with neither excit=\r\nement nor \ndisappointment. But one should NOT run after them, for they are =\r\nneither \nnecessary nor sufficient for self-realization and liberation. \n\n=\r\n=C2=A0 \nVivekananda used the same principle when Ramakirishna proposed to g=\r\nive his \nsiddhis to Vivekananda. He asked whether the siddhis will enable h=\r\nim to realize \ngod. Ramakrishna said no. Vivekananda firmly declined the of=\r\nfer then! Of course, \nwhen Ramakrishna gave them anyway later, he accepted =\r\nthem. Vivekananda&#39;s two \nactions demonstrate Vasishtha&#39;s instructions well.=\r\n \n\n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nLet us use the analogy of climbing a hi=\r\nll. Climbing hill is one&#39;s spiritual \nsadhana. Reaching the top is liberati=\r\non. Different people climb the hill from \ndifferent sides and using differe=\r\nnt paths. There may be trees with nice fruits \non the sides of the road. Th=\r\ney are siddhis or special abilities. \n\n=C2=A0 \nIf one gets distracted, star=\r\nts climbing the trees and collecting fruits, one&#39;s \njourney gets delayed an=\r\nd one may not reach the top. That is why Vasishtha says a \nseeker of Self d=\r\noes not pursue any siddhis. \n\n=C2=A0 \nBut if some fruits fall in one&#39;s lap =\r\nby themselves, one can keep them. \nSimilarly, siddhis that come to one by t=\r\nhemselves can be accepted by a seeker of \nSelf. \n\n=C2=A0 \nNow an important =\r\ndistinction: \n=C2=A0 \nThere are some trees that are found at lower altitude=\r\ns also, but some really \nspecial trees are found at very high altitudes onl=\r\ny. If one has such a fruit, it \nshows that one has climbed great heights. S=\r\nimilarly, some siddhis do not mean \nmuch, but some siddhis are very special=\r\n and only really elevated sadhakas can \nobtain them (whether by trying or w=\r\nithout trying). If a sadhakas demonstrates \nsuch a siddhi, you can see that=\r\n one progressed a lot. However, the key is that \none who climbed the same o=\r\nr more distance may not have that or any other fruit. \n\n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nUnlike in the example of climbing hill, which is an external=\r\n activity, spiritual \nprogress in real life is *internal*. There is NO way =\r\nfor anyone to know for sure \nhow much progress one has made, how much self-=\r\ncontrol one has internally and \nwhat exactly goes on in one&#39;s mind. We may =\r\ntry to judge it from external factors \nsuch as actions, words etc, but it i=\r\ns not necessarily accurate. \n\n=C2=A0 \nHere, some people swayed by siddhis m=\r\nay be tempted to use one&#39;s siddhis to judge \nhow high one climbed. But that=\r\n is faulty. One person who reached the absolute \ntop may not have any fruit=\r\ns, while one person who still has ways to climb may \nhave gotten some reall=\r\ny nice fruit. Using externaslly demonstrable siddhis that \nare neither nece=\r\nssary nor sufficient for Self-realization as a measure of one&#39;s \nprogress i=\r\ns unsound. \n\n=C2=A0 \nGiven that spiritual progress is internal, how can we =\r\njudge it and compare \npeople then? Well, we need not and should not. Only a=\r\n sarvaantaryaami - a \nperfected being who has access to each being&#39;s intern=\r\nal state - can do that. \n\n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nRajarshi, you ar=\r\ne assuming that Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is a Paramahamsa on \nVimalananda&#39;s =\r\nscale. You are concluding that Ramakrishna is a Paramahamsa; \nAbhedananda, =\r\nVivekananda etc are lower than that; Vimalananda is a rishi; and \nhence Vim=\r\nalananda is superior to Abhedananda and Vivekananda by 2pwr16 to 2. \n\n=C2=\r\n=A0 \nIs Paramahamsa Nithyananda, who was caught in a sex scandal, also a Pa=\r\nramahamsa \nbecause he is known so? See, how people are famously known may o=\r\nr may not \nreflect their spiritual stature. Real spiritual stature is inter=\r\nnal and you \ncannot see it. \n\n=C2=A0 \nWe do not know who Ramakrishna Parama=\r\nhamsa really is. He may not be just a \nparamahamsa on Vimalananda&#39;s scale, =\r\nbut be a siddha or a natha or even a rishi. \nHe may even be Vishnu himself,=\r\n as he himself said and some religious experts of \nthat time declared based=\r\n on various signs. If Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is Vishnu \nhimself, Vivekanan=\r\nda, Abhedananda etc can definitely be rishis or naths in \nVimalananda&#39;s sca=\r\nle. If your argument is that they cannot be because they did \nnot demonstra=\r\nte siddhis compatible with that status, that is a non-point as I \nexplained=\r\n above. The disagreement between then boils down a difference in the \nrelev=\r\nance and importance of externally demonstrated siddhis. \n\n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nWhy this is relevant and I spent some time on this is tha=\r\nt some people seem to \nhave misconceptions. The take home for some people f=\r\nrom some books describing \nmiracles and siddhis may be that siddhis are imp=\r\nortant. \n\n=C2=A0 \nVasishtha is not only a rishi, but one of saptarshis. Ple=\r\nase read what he taught \nLord Rama in Yoga Vaasishtham. It is the essence o=\r\nf Veda and Upanishad. It will \nbalance your views and mould your attitude. =\r\nRead Yoga Vaasishtham. Siddhis are \nneither necessary nor sufficient for se=\r\nlf-realization. Don&#39;t be distracted by \nthem or be infatuated with them. \n\n=\r\n=C2=A0 \nThe goal of sadhana is that your notions of &quot;this is I and these ar=\r\ne mine&quot; get \nsubtler and subtler and hold of six internal enemies on you be=\r\ncomes weaker and \nweaker. Others may or may not be able to see and judge yo=\r\nur progress, but you \nknow your progress and weaknesses the best. THAT is t=\r\nhe crux and siddhis have no \nrelevance or meaning. Any fascination for them=\r\n will set you back in your \nsadhana. \n\n=C2=A0 \nBest regards, \nNarasimha \n--=\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------- \n=C2=A0 F=\r\nree Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings, \n&quot;Do It Yours=\r\nelf&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and Pitri Tarpana: \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 http://www.VedicAstrologer.org \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Films th=\r\nat make a difference: http://SaraswatiFilms.org \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 S=\r\npirituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom \n=C2=A0 Jyotish wri=\r\ntings: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Twitter ID: @homam108 \n---------------------------=\r\n---------------------------------------- \n=C2=A0 \n--- In vedic-wisdom@yahoo=\r\ngroups.com, Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt; wrote: \n&gt; \n&gt; Namaste friends, \n&gt; \n&gt;=\r\n There was a long friendly ;-) exchange between Rajarshi and me on Friday \n=\r\n&gt; (July 29) on twitter on measuring spiritual caliber. This came from the \n=\r\n&gt; context of Rajarshi&#39;s comments on the &quot;ma