gn=3Dleft=\r\n&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B=\r\n&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerd=\r\nana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000=\r\n000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s teaching to Lord Ram=\r\na is clear in Yoga Vaasishtham. The goal of existence and sadhana is self-r=\r\nealization. Siddhis are to be neither specifically sought nor specifically =\r\navoided, by a seeker of Self. If Nature gives one some siddhi(s), one shoul=\r\nd accept them with neither excitement nor disappointment. But one should NO=\r\nT run after them, for they are neither necessary nor sufficient for self-re=\r\nalization and liberation. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT col=\r\nor=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DI=\r\nV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;Vivekana=\r\nnda used the same principle when Ramakirishna proposed to give his siddhis =\r\nto Vivekananda. He asked whether the siddhis will enable him to realize god=\r\n. Ramakrishna said no. Vivekananda firmly declined the offer then! Of cours=\r\ne, when Ramakrishna gave them anyway later, he accepted them. Vivekananda&#39;s=\r\n two actions demonstrate Vasishtha&#39;s instructions well. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DI=\r\nV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&n=\r\nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2=\r\n face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dlef=\r\nt&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT=\r\n&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;=\r\n&lt;I&gt;Let us use the analogy of climbing a hill. Climbing hill is one&#39;s spirit=\r\nual sadhana. Reaching the top is liberation. Different people climb the hil=\r\nl from different sides and using different paths. There may be trees with n=\r\nice fruits on the sides of the road. They are siddhis or special abilities.=\r\n &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 fac=\r\ne=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT colo=\r\nr=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;If one gets distracted, starts cl=\r\nimbing the trees and collecting fruits, one&#39;s journey gets delayed and one =\r\nmay not reach the top. That is why Vasishtha says a seeker of Self does not=\r\n pursue any siddhis. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D=\r\n#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV ali=\r\ngn=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;But if some f=\r\nruits fall in one&#39;s lap by themselves, one can keep them. Similarly, siddhi=\r\ns that come to one by themselves can be accepted by a seeker of Self. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;=\r\n/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVe=\r\nrdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#0=\r\n00000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;Now an important distinction: &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;=\r\n/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdan=\r\na&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#00000=\r\n0 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;There are some trees that are found at lowe=\r\nr altitudes also, but some really special trees are found at very high alti=\r\ntudes only. If one has such a fruit, it shows that one has climbed great he=\r\nights. Similarly, some siddhis do not mean much, but some siddhis are very =\r\nspecial and only really elevated sadhakas can obtain them (whether by tryin=\r\ng or without trying). If a sadhakas demonstrates such a siddhi, you can see=\r\n that one progressed a lot. However, the key is that one who climbed the sa=\r\nme or more distance may not have that or any other fruit. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/=\r\nDIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;=\r\n&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=\r\n=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbs=\r\np;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=\r\n=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;=\r\n&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerda=\r\nna&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;Unlike in the example of climbing hill, which is an external activ=\r\nity, spiritual progress in real life is *internal*. There is NO way for any=\r\none to know for sure how much progress one has made, how much self-control =\r\none has internally and what exactly goes on in one&#39;s mind. We may try to ju=\r\ndge it from external factors such as actions, words etc, but it is not nece=\r\nssarily accurate. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#00=\r\n0000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=\r\n=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;Here, some peop=\r\nle swayed by siddhis may be tempted to use one&#39;s siddhis to judge how high =\r\none climbed. But that is faulty. One person who reached the absolute top ma=\r\ny not have any fruits, while one person who still has ways to climb may hav=\r\ne gotten some really nice fruit. Using externaslly demonstrable siddhis tha=\r\nt are neither necessary nor sufficient for Self-realization as a measure of=\r\n one&#39;s progress is unsound. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT c=\r\nolor=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;=\r\nDIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;Given =\r\nthat spiritual progress is internal, how can we judge it and compare people=\r\n then? Well, we need not and should not. Only a sarvaantaryaami - a perfect=\r\ned being who has access to each being&#39;s internal state - can do that. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;=\r\n/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVe=\r\nrdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#0=\r\n00000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;D=\r\nIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; =\r\n&lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=\r\n=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;Rajarshi, you are assuming that Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is=\r\n a Paramahamsa on Vimalananda&#39;s scale. You are concluding that Ramakrishna =\r\nis a Paramahamsa; Abhedananda, Vivekananda etc are lower than that; Vimalan=\r\nanda is a rishi; and hence Vimalananda is superior to Abhedananda and Vivek=\r\nananda by 2pwr16 to 2. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=\r\n=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV =\r\nalign=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;Is Paramah=\r\namsa Nithyananda, who was caught in a sex scandal, also a Paramahamsa becau=\r\nse he is known so? See, how people are famously known may or may not reflec=\r\nt their spiritual stature. Real spiritual stature is internal and you canno=\r\nt see it. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;FONT color=3D#000000 siz=\r\ne=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;\n&lt;DIV align=3Dleft&gt;&lt;=\r\nFONT color=3D#000000 size=3D2 face=3DVerdana&gt;&lt;B&gt;&lt;I&gt;We do not know who Ramak=\r\nrishna Paramahamsa really is. He may not be just a paramahamsa on Vimalanan=\r\nda&#39;s scale, but be a siddha or a natha or even a rishi. He may even be Vish=\r\nnu himself, as he himself said and some religious experts of that time decl=\r\nared based on various signs. If Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is Vishnu himself, =\r\nVivekananda, Abhedananda etc can definitely be rishis or naths in Vimalanan=\r\nda&#39;s scale. If your argument is that they cannot be because they did not de=\r\nmonstrate siddhis compatible with that status, that is a non-point as I exp=\r\nlained above. The disagreement between then boils down a difference in the =\r\nrelevance and importance of externally demonstrated siddhis. &lt;/I&gt;&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/FONT=\r\n&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;